## Backend watcher note (IMPORTANT for deploy-test)

The `mw-backend` push (commit 6876837) was received by GitHub. The Surface
auto-deploy watcher should pull it and restart waitress within ~30-60s of the
push. At the time this step completed, the Surface had not yet rotated to the
new process -- `GET /healthstack/services` returned 404 from the old Flask app.

Confirmed this run (2026-06-14, deploy step second pass): Flask IS running (`/health` 200,
`/repsetta/exercises` returns JSON exercise list). The healthstack blueprint is syntactically
valid (Python `ast.parse` PASS). It is registered in `server.py` lines 274-276. The
`mw-backend` origin/main is at commit 6876837 ("Add HealthStack Flask blueprint with JWT
auth and booking endpoints", committed 2026-06-14 19:40:34 -0500).

The Surface auto-deploy watcher (`auto-deploy.ps1`) polls every 30s and does
`git pull --ff-only` + Flask restart. The watcher may need a manual restart on
the Surface if it has not already picked up the commit.

deploy-test should allow ~60s from the time it starts before treating a 404 on
`/healthstack/*` as a hard failure. Retry a few times with short backoff.

Blueprint file: `mw-backend/healthstack_blueprint.py` -- imports `jwt`, `flask`,
`secrets`, `datetime`, `functools`. All confirmed importable locally; no missing deps.

